uire replacing collateral or proportional paydowns. Discuss your multi-property strategy with our team to determine whether blanket financing or separate loans better serve your situation."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "What commercial loan programs work for foreign investors?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Foreign national loan programs specifically accommodate international investors without U.S. credit history, Social Security numbers, or domestic income. These programs focus on property fundamentals and down payment capacity rather than U.S. credit metrics. Required down payments typically exceed domestic borrower requirements, and rates reflect additional perceived risk, but terms remain competitive enough making U.S. commercial real estate attractive for international portfolio diversification. See our foreign national case studies for examples."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "How quickly can commercial loans close?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Closing timelines vary dramatically by program. Hard money and bridge loans can close in 7-14 days when documentation is ready. DSCR loans typically close in 21-30 days. Traditional commercial mortgages and construction loans often require 45-60 days. SBA loans can take 60-90 days due to government approval requirements. We provide 24-hour pre-approvals across programs, positioning you for fastest possible closings when timing matters."}}]};
